<br>
I finally got back there tonight after my fiasco in the minefield last week.  My DSL router broke, so it was 1 PC action, no clarity from my chanter.  I also skipped FotH in case I had to egress, didn't want to be without SoW.  So no mana regen, just mano-a-mobo.  Noone had mentioned how much these guys resist snare/root, or break root early, or that they had TONS of HP.  After several resisted roots and many early breaks, I gave up and used the free necklace root, which was resisted even more (2/3s of the time), but was free so at least it didn't take any mana.<br>
<br>
I wound up having to cast root so much, because of early breaks, that there was basically no medding, and with no regen, went OOM fairly quickly.  Spent the last 7 of the 14 minutes it took OOM, and just spamming free root and DoD.<br>
Toughest fight I ever had!<br>
<br>
So what do these guys have, about 15kHP (legionnaire)?<br>
<br>
Needless to say, no earring, just a coterie gorget, and a vampyre fang (what's that for?)<br>
<br>
It was a lot of fun, but needless to say, I won't be spending anymore time there without epic (or at least 2nd PC).<br>
<br>
Tat <p>Tatanka WolfDancer, 58th Druid<BR>
